Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.22,0:01:27.15,lassie episode,[title],0,0,0,,{TIME:82228,87150}{\blur0.5\fad(500,0)\pos(320,295)}Goodbye, Lassie
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.02,0:01:32.19,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:89027,92196}So she got here on this boat?{NOTE:dog gender}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.19,0:01:37.70,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:92196,97702}Yeah. I mean, the collar\NI found fits her perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.70,0:01:40.87,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:97702,100872}And she replied when I read\Nthe name written on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.49,0:01:43.83,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:102498,103833}Right, Lassie?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.08,0:01:46.25,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:105084,106252}See?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.71,0:01:50.29,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:108713,110298}Grandpa!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.29,0:01:51.75,lassie default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:110298,111758}Oh, hello, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.75,0:01:54.71,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:111758,114719}Do you know\Nthe owner of this boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.71,0:01:55.80,lassie default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:114719,115803}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.80,0:01:57.34,lassie default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:115803,117347}Ah, that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.34,0:02:01.47,lassie default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:117347,121476}It's been here\Nfor two or three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.47,0:02:03.97,lassie default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:121476,123978}Maybe it has no owner?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.22,0:02:06.52,lassie default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:125229,126522}Take a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.19,0:02:10.02,lassie default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:127190,130026}The rope it was tied with\Nis now cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.02,0:02:13.07,lassie default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:130026,133071}The boat probably couldn't stand\Nits owners and escaped them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.07,0:02:13.98,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:133071,133988}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.98,0:02:16.49,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:133988,136491}By escaping its owners, you mean
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.49,0:02:19.03,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:136491,139035}the rope broke and the boat\Ndrifted here on its own?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.16,0:02:21.82,lassie default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:140161,141829}Maybe so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.82,0:02:26.62,lassie default,Grandpa,0,0,0,,{TIME:141829,146626}In the end, you won't know the truth\Nuntil you ask the boat itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:40.01,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:156469,160014}I don't think the boat is gonna\Ntell us where it came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.93,0:02:44.01,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:160932,164018}Hey, Lassie,\Nwhere did you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.39,0:02:50.69,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:168398,170692}Is it all right to move it\Nwithout anyone's permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.69,0:02:53.94,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:170692,173945}It's in a good cause.\NWe have to find its owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.94,0:02:54.82,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:173945,174821}Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.82,0:02:56.11,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:174821,176114}Wait for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.45,0:03:03.91,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:180451,183913}If we learn where\Nthe boat came from,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.62,0:03:07.75,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:184622,187750}we may find Lassie's mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.75,0:03:08.96,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:187750,188960}Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.96,0:03:12.50,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:188960,192505}I see. So once you find her owner,\Nyou'll have to give her back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.50,0:03:14.29,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:192505,194298}Naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.29,0:03:15.96,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:194298,195967}Naturally, huh…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.96,0:03:22.59,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:195967,202598}Yes. If Lassie lives with her mother,\Nshe'll be much happier.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.01,0:03:26.47,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:204016,206477}If you say so, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.77,0:03:28.89,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:207770,208896}It's an airplane!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:33.35,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:209939,213359}This plane belongs to a family\Nwe were recently delivering to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.35,0:03:34.77,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:213359,214777}Dad told me so.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.78,0:03:41.78,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:217780,221784}Now that I think of it, when I met you\Nfor the first time, there was an airplane, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.87,0:03:47.49,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:223870,227498}If it wasn't for that plane,\NI wouldn't meet Lassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.09,0:04:04.22,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:242096,244223}This is the road to school!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.80,0:04:06.68,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:244807,246684}It's the bridge we always cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.76,0:04:09.39,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:247769,249395}Oh? John and Colin.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.39,0:04:11.18,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:249395,251189}Where did you get this boat?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.85,0:04:16.31,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:254859,256319}Guess what!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.31,0:04:19.19,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:256319,259197}We're searching for Lassie's mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.19,0:04:20.03,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:259197,260031}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.03,0:04:22.15,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:260031,262158}Have you found\Nthe owner of the puppy?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.15,0:04:23.78,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:262158,263785}Not yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.78,0:04:27.70,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:264786,267705}But I'm sure that\Nwe'll find Lassie's mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.70,0:04:31.91,lassie default,Sandy,0,0,0,,{TIME:267705,271918}So… John! Wait!\NHey, listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.62,0:04:34.37,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:272627,274378}The backyards\Nnear the town square.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.37,0:04:35.33,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:274378,275338}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.33,0:04:37.79,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:275338,277799}This is the first time I see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.17,0:04:41.21,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:279175,281219}I saw him, I saw him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.22,0:04:44.01,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:283221,284013}John!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.09,0:04:48.55,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:286098,288559}Mr. Curry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.23,0:04:54.44,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:292230,294440}She's so beautiful, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.36,0:05:01.61,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:298361,301614}From the river, our town\Nlooks like another place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.61,0:05:02.99,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:301614,302990}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.12,0:05:12.41,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:311123,312416}Dr. Hopper!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.62,0:05:18.33,lassie default,Dr. Hopper,0,0,0,,{TIME:313626,318339}Hello. You're Carraclough's son, right?\NThat's a nice boat you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.33,0:05:19.50,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:318339,319507}Thanks. But…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.71,0:05:23.71,lassie default,Dr. Hopper,0,0,0,,{TIME:320716,323719}This reminds me…\NWait, what was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.59,0:05:29.01,lassie default,Dr. Hopper,0,0,0,,{TIME:324595,329016}Ah, right! I remember seeing\Nthat puppy on this boat a few days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.01,0:05:31.64,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:329016,331644}Dr. Hopper,\Nyou've seen it before?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.64,0:05:35.69,lassie default,Dr. Hopper,0,0,0,,{TIME:331644,335690}Yes. They must've floated\Ndown here from upstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.69,0:05:36.35,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:335690,336357}John.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.35,0:05:37.06,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:336357,337066}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.56,0:05:40.06,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:337567,340069}Thank you very much, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.06,0:05:45.99,lassie default,Dr. Hopper,0,0,0,,{TIME:340069,345992}No problem, just don't tell\Nyour mother that you saw me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.04,0:05:57.21,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:355042,357211}What, you're scared?\NYou're such a coward.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.30,0:06:06.88,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:365303,366888}Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.29,0:06:38.66,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:397293,398669}We've came pretty far.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.66,0:06:40.50,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:398669,400504}How long are we going\Nto oar like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.71,0:06:42.79,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:401714,402798}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.59,0:06:45.25,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:403591,405259}It's a steamer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.31,0:07:00.35,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:418314,420358}Lassie!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.02,0:07:03.56,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:422026,423569}Wait for me, Lassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.36,0:07:06.48,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:425363,426489}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.78,0:07:10.74,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:428783,430743}Lassie!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.91,0:07:18.41,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:436916,438417}This is dangerous, Lassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.41,0:07:21.71,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:438417,441712}If you're not careful,\Nyou'll get ran over.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.00,0:07:26.55,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:445007,446550}What's this wheel doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.55,0:07:27.55,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:446550,447551}John!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.55,0:07:28.46,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:447551,448469}Hey, John!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.72,0:07:31.59,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:449720,451597}Here, look. Check this rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.26,0:07:35.60,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:452264,455601}It's the same rope\Nas the one on the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.22,0:07:38.10,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:456227,458104}So, this means…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.10,0:07:41.39,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:458104,461399}Look, they're exactly the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.39,0:07:44.48,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:461399,464485}So Lassie drifted down from here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.98,0:07:49.49,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:464986,469490}Thank goodness, Lassie.\NYou're going to see your mom soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.61,0:07:51.99,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:470616,471993}It went easier than I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.33,0:08:01.25,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:478332,481252}Hey, what's the racket?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.25,0:08:05.38,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:481252,485381}You two rascals, why are you making\Nnoise around other people's houses?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.34,0:08:09.96,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:486340,489969}Hey! It's the boat\NI lost the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.38,0:08:17.72,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:493389,497727}Y-You got it wrong, sir. It drifted\Non its own and we've brought it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.72,0:08:19.68,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:497727,499687}I'm telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:20.85,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:499687,500855}I'm not convinced.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.02,0:08:22.69,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:502023,502690}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.02,0:08:24.31,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:503024,504316}Where did you find this dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.31,0:08:28.19,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:504316,508195}Uh, she…\NUhm… You see…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.19,0:08:30.15,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:508195,510156}It's Lassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.15,0:08:33.53,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:512158,513534}This means…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.45,0:08:37.74,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:514452,517747}Sir, you know Lassie?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.74,0:08:40.54,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:517747,520541}Of course I do.\NShe's my dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.54,0:08:41.62,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:520541,521625}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.66,0:08:44.62,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:522668,524628}Do you want me to say this again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.62,0:08:48.04,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:524628,528049}No, everything's fine.\NI'll return her immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.88,0:08:49.88,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:528883,529884}But…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.17,0:08:51.13,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:530176,531135}But what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.88,0:08:55.38,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:531886,535389}I found her about to get crushed\Nunder a herd of sheep,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.38,0:08:58.80,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:535389,538809}so I rescued her and\Nshe stayed with me for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.80,0:09:02.31,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:538809,542313}Please give me a moment\Nto say goodbye to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.31,0:09:03.77,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:542313,543773}Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.31,0:09:07.10,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:544315,547109}Fine, do whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.10,0:09:08.65,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:547109,548652}Bring her to me\Nwhen you're finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:19.58,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:556744,559580}Isn't it great, Lassie?\NWe've found your owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.87,0:09:22.29,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:560873,562291}Lassie?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.66,0:09:25.29,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:562666,565294}Your mom must be\Nworried about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.29,0:09:26.79,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:565294,566796}Stay healthy, Lassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.00,0:09:30.29,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:568005,570299}Don't forget about me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.88,0:09:36.05,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:572885,576055}All right.\NNow go to your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.64,0:09:45.48,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:582645,585481}Come on, go! Don't you want\Nto see your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.36,0:09:49.94,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:589360,589944}Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.40,0:09:53.36,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:591403,593364}Lassie, that's not the way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.57,0:10:02.66,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:599578,602665}I'm going, I'm going,\Nyou impatient bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.66,0:10:05.62,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:602665,605626}I'm opening the valve, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:07.16,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:605626,607169}Whoa, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.16,0:10:09.83,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:607169,609839}It's not a place to play!\NGet out of there!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.46,0:10:11.92,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:610464,611924}It's not a playground.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.71,0:10:14.96,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:612716,614969}I remember about you, for crying out loud!\NA minute won't save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.96,0:10:19.26,lassie default,Sailor,0,0,0,,{TIME:614969,619265}Hurry up, old man!\NDid the pump break again or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.30,0:10:24.60,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:620307,624603}Watch your mouth!\NOur pump is the best around—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.43,0:10:29.44,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:626438,629441}Damn, I have no time for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.40,0:10:37.11,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:635406,637116}Hey, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.57,0:10:41.12,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:637575,641120}Come here and lend me a hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.12,0:10:49.50,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:644123,649503}Listen, Lassie, let's leave this wheel\Nand go greet your owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.50,0:10:50.21,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:649503,650212}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.21,0:10:53.17,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:650212,653174}Good. Pull it harder, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.55,0:11:00.18,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:656552,660181}What's the matter?\NYou can't move it any further?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.76,0:11:03.93,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:662766,663934}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.93,0:11:06.77,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:663934,666770}First we close the gate,\Nthen we raise the level of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.14,0:11:11.77,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:667146,671775}Then we let the boat in and close the gate\Nbehind it, after that we let the water out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.27,0:11:15.73,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:672276,675738}Finally, once the water's low,\Nwe open the gate and let the boat out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.73,0:11:17.32,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:675738,677323}How's it going?\NDid you close it yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.53,0:11:20.32,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:678532,680326}Yeah, somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.29,0:11:29.62,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:686290,689627}But why did he ask you, Colin?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.54,0:11:34.13,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:690544,694131}I don't know, but\Nhe sure works his men hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.13,0:11:35.50,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:694131,695507}What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.34,0:11:38.88,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:696342,698886}Have you said your\Ngoodbyes to the dog, kid?
Comment: 0,0:11:50.43,0:11:50.43,[chapter],[chapter],0,0,0,,{TIME:710439,710439}Part B
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.27,0:11:59.99,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:713275,719990}Look at yourself. A bit of honest work\Nand you stop fooling around.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.49,0:12:04.16,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:722493,724161}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.16,0:12:06.24,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:724161,726247}Give me a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.16,0:12:08.49,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:727164,728499}You can't do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.99,0:12:10.66,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:728999,730668}I'm taking it now, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.21,0:12:17.38,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:733212,737383}And don't think of coming here again.\NGo to your moms.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.46,0:12:21.55,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:738467,741553}Sir, are you\Nthe operator of this lock?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:24.34,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:741553,744348}No, I'm a mailman.\NDon't ask stupid questions, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.34,0:12:26.64,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:744348,746642}Do you live here alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.64,0:12:27.47,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:746642,747476}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.47,0:12:30.81,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:747476,750813}Don't you have a family\Nother than this puppy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.81,0:12:33.14,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:750813,753148}I don't. What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.44,0:12:36.44,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:754441,756443}I guess there's nothing we can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.90,0:12:42.28,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:759905,762283}You get here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.28,0:12:44.28,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:762283,764285}If you misbehave, I'll eat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.95,0:12:50.04,lassie default,Sailor,0,0,0,,{TIME:765953,770040}Come on, old man.\NOpen the other gate already.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.04,0:12:51.91,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:770040,771917}I told you to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.06,0:13:22.28,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:798068,802281}I'm sure that man\Nloves Lassie, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.28,0:13:23.57,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:802281,803574}I wouldn't be so sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.65,0:13:26.32,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:804658,806327}Oh, right, I forgot\Nto tell him something.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.32,0:13:27.36,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:806327,807369}John?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.54,0:13:34.37,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:811540,814376}What is it?\NYou're that kid again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.37,0:13:35.62,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:814376,815627}What do you want this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.62,0:13:36.92,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:815627,816920}Sir…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.46,0:13:41.13,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:817463,821133}Lassie drinks milk\Nfrom a baby bottle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.13,0:13:42.25,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:821133,822259}However…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.13,0:13:44.17,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:823135,824178}What of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.17,0:13:48.55,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:825179,828557}I think she could be trained\Nto drink from a plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.55,0:13:49.60,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:828557,829600}So I was thinking…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.60,0:13:51.85,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:829600,831852}Err… Sir, what if…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.56,0:13:54.98,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:832561,834980}Don't you have better things to do\Nthan bothering people?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.56,0:13:59.77,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:836565,839777}I'm not gonna spend\Nevery day training it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.77,0:14:02.61,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:839777,842613}If it can't drink milk\Non its own, so be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.61,0:14:05.49,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:842613,845491}"So be it"? So what's going\Nto happen to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:08.24,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:845491,848243}How can I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.87,0:14:11.53,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:849870,851538}How can I know…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.28,0:14:16.16,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:852289,856168}Well, the world was never easy\Nto live in to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.16,0:14:17.21,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:856168,857211}John…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.21,0:14:17.75,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:857211,857753}Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.29,0:14:20.25,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:858295,860255}Let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.67,0:14:30.47,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:866678,870474}Listen, John, let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.47,0:14:32.47,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:870474,872476}But that looks so interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.60,0:14:36.27,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:873602,876271}Ah, it started to move!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.83,0:14:56.45,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:893831,896458}Now you're spying on people!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.84,0:15:09.38,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:905843,909388}What is your problem?\NWhy were you looking through my window?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.38,0:15:11.72,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:909388,911723}But I was so surprised!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.72,0:15:14.89,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:911723,914893}I didn't know people could have\Nsuch amazing machines in their houses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.89,0:15:17.52,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:914893,917521}Can I go inside\Nand take a look at it, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.52,0:15:19.48,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:917521,919481}Absolutely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.48,0:15:21.40,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:919481,921400}That includes peeking\Nthrough my windows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.40,0:15:22.31,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:921400,922317}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.31,0:15:23.19,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:922317,923193}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.19,0:15:24.69,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:923193,924695}Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.94,0:15:26.48,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:924945,926488}Stop fooling around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.86,0:15:31.82,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:929867,931827}It's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:33.28,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:931827,933287}I can't find one anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.66,0:15:38.62,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:935664,938625}I won't repeat myself twice.\NGet out of my house, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.62,0:15:41.67,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:938625,941670}Don't you have a doghouse, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.67,0:15:42.42,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:941670,942421}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.42,0:15:44.84,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:942421,944840}A doghouse?\NThere's no such thing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.84,0:15:48.84,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:944840,948844}Huh? You don't have one?\NThen where do you keep it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.17,0:15:51.13,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:949178,951138}Why do you even care?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.13,0:15:54.85,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:951138,954850}I don't have time to answer\Nyour countless questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.18,0:15:57.56,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:956185,957561}Now get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.56,0:15:59.06,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:957561,959062}No time?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.06,0:16:02.64,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:959062,962649}A boat arrives every once in a while,\Nbut other than that, what else are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.64,0:16:05.44,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:962649,965444}Another question?\NLeave me alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.52,0:16:09.57,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:966528,969573}Hey, sir! Don't close the doors!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.19,0:16:12.28,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:970199,972284}I want to ask you something else!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.28,0:16:14.28,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:972284,974286}Give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.28,0:16:15.82,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:974286,975829}But it's important.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.74,0:16:18.58,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:976747,978582}John, that's enough.\NLet's go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.58,0:16:21.41,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:978582,981418}But it really is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.00,0:16:26.50,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:983003,986507}I've had enough.\NFine, I'll answer one last question.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.50,0:16:27.63,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:986507,987633}What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.67,0:16:33.13,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:988675,993138}Uhm, what do you have\Nto eat for today, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.01,0:16:36.89,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:995015,996892}What's for dinner?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.89,0:16:38.85,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:996892,998852}Is this what you wanted to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.85,0:16:40.14,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:998852,1000145}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.89,0:16:43.94,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1002898,1003941}It's canned food.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.94,0:16:44.98,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1003941,1004983}Canned food?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.98,0:16:48.69,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1004983,1008695}Yes. Canned food in the morning.\NCanned food in the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.69,0:16:51.78,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1008695,1011782}I don't have time to cook\Nso my food is just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:55.78,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1013283,1015786}Oh, thank goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.32,0:17:00.91,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1016328,1020916}It's not like it's good, you know.\NThere's nothing else for me to eat here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.29,0:17:07.29,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1022292,1027297}Kid, why are you\Ninterested in my food?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.83,0:17:13.30,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1027839,1033303}If you didn't have food to eat,\Nyou might have to eat Lassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.30,0:17:14.51,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1033303,1034513}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.51,0:17:19.97,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1034513,1039977}You think I meant what I said to it before?\NThat I'm going to eat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.52,0:17:23.68,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1041520,1043689}Maybe you weren't serious, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.68,0:17:28.98,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1043689,1048986}I don't see Lassie's mom anywhere,\Nand I can only guess the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.98,0:17:29.90,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:1048986,1049903}Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.90,0:17:32.28,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:1049903,1052281}You don't see Lassie's mom here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.28,0:17:34.44,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1052281,1054449}Where is Lassie's mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.44,0:17:37.49,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1054449,1057494}I didn't eat her, that's for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.91,0:17:42.12,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1057911,1062124}Sir! Tell me where she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.12,0:17:47.54,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1062124,1067546}We want to find Lassie's mom and\Nbring them together. We came this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.54,0:17:50.09,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1067546,1070090}Why isn't she here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.09,0:17:52.80,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:1070090,1072801}Is she really not here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.80,0:17:55.09,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1072801,1075095}Yes, I looked all around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.09,0:17:59.51,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:1075095,1079516}I bet he's a liar.\NHe's not the owner of Lassie!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.60,0:18:04.10,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1081602,1084104}I'm not a liar!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.10,0:18:05.43,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1084104,1085439}I hate lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.89,0:18:10.73,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1087899,1090736}It's because of that flat tire.\NIt's all because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.73,0:18:14.15,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1090736,1094156}A flat tire? Ah, that wheel…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.86,0:18:18.36,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1096867,1098368}You know what\NI'm talking about, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.36,0:18:22.53,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1098368,1102539}No, but earlier when Lassie escaped me,\Nshe immediately ran to a car wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.20,0:18:28.46,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1104207,1108462}A few days ago there was\Na car on this road with a flat tire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:32.46,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1108754,1112466}The owner said he was from a foreign country\Nand was accompanied by a big Collie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.13,0:18:37.88,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1113133,1117888}When the driver was busy replacing\Nthe tire, this guy fled away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:39.26,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1117888,1119264}He couldn't find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.97,0:18:42.93,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1119973,1122934}The port was far away and\Nhe couldn't stay any longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.93,0:18:44.97,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1122934,1124978}So he decided to leave it alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.97,0:18:49.85,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1124978,1129858}He also asked me to\Ntake care of it, if I ever find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.85,0:18:53.61,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1129858,1133612}See? Which is why this puppy\Nbelongs to me now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.61,0:18:56.36,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1133612,1136365}He left it under my care,\Nso I have no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.57,0:19:00.78,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1138575,1140786}Stop with that bark!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.78,0:19:04.16,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1140786,1144164}You're not taking care of her at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.16,0:19:07.50,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1144164,1147501}You have to promise me\Nthat you will take good care of Lassie!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.87,0:19:09.67,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1147876,1149670}Are you stupid?\NWatch where we are!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.21,0:19:13.50,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1152214,1153507}What are you doing, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.50,0:19:17.38,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1153507,1157386}I thought it was not possible\Nfor me to take care of her,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.38,0:19:20.84,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1157386,1160847}so I had decided to take her\Nto her real owners!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.84,0:19:22.51,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1160847,1162516}And yet…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.51,0:19:26.72,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1162516,1166728}You think if you're persistent enough,\NI'll let you have it like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.72,0:19:27.85,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1166728,1167854}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.85,0:19:29.85,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1167854,1169856}No? Don't lie to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.85,0:19:31.52,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1169856,1171525}I'm not lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.52,0:19:32.94,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1171525,1172943}Let me hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.48,0:19:37.03,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1174486,1177030}Admit you just want\Nher for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.03,0:19:38.40,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1177030,1178407}I don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.57,0:19:41.49,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1179574,1181493}As if I can believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.74,0:19:46.58,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1184746,1186581}Think your barking\Nis going to help?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.58,0:19:48.50,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:1186581,1188500}John, are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.54,0:19:53.58,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1191545,1193588}Well, don't come here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.58,0:19:57.67,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1193588,1197676}You're a liar and unable\Nto take care of it. Go home, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.42,0:20:01.26,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1198427,1201263}I'm not going anywhere\Nuntil you promise me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.26,0:20:02.72,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1201263,1202723}Stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.10,0:20:06.35,lassie default,Colin,0,0,0,,{TIME:1205100,1206351}Oh! John!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.98,0:20:13.81,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1210981,1213817}I can't leave you now.\NHere, grab onto this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:19.53,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1213817,1219531}No! I won't grab it, not before you\Npromise me to take good care of Lassie!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.78,0:20:21.70,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1219781,1221700}This is not the time\Nfor worthless arguments!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.70,0:20:25.28,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1221700,1225287}Promise me that\Nyou won't bully her again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.28,0:20:27.53,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1225287,1227539}I'm sorry I wasn't born\Nwith a pretty attitude!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.53,0:20:29.70,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1227539,1229708}I never planned to bully it, all right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.96,0:20:35.88,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1232961,1235881}Look, it's a ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.29,0:20:38.88,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1236298,1238884}Hurry up and get your butt\Noutta there or you'll regret it, kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.26,0:20:45.05,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1242262,1245056}All right, all right!\NI promise you!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:20:59.23,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1258195,1259237}Lassie.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.19,0:21:03.53,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1260197,1263533}This mister lives alone,\Nso take care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.53,0:21:06.24,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1263533,1266244}Hmph. As if it could\Nunderstand you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.07,0:21:09.28,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1268079,1269289}Oh…
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.28,0:21:10.83,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1269289,1270832}Here, it's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.83,0:21:14.46,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1270832,1274461}But I brought her to you\Nbecause you are her real owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.46,0:21:18.04,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1274461,1278048}It's true that I made\Na promise to take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.04,0:21:22.34,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1278048,1282344}But in the end,\Nit doesn't matter who gets to raise it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.17,0:21:26.34,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1283178,1286348}Doing it myself would be a pain\Nin the butt, so I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.81,0:21:35.60,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1291812,1295607}Come visit me again some day,\Nthe three of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.60,0:21:39.31,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1295607,1299319}I will offer you\Nsome fresh seafood then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.31,0:21:40.52,lassie default,Water lock operator,0,0,0,,{TIME:1299319,1300529}You hear me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.52,0:21:42.86,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1300529,1302864}Yes! We will come, for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.24,0:21:47.16,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1304241,1307160}Now, Lassie, let's go.\NTo our home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.16,0:21:50.70,lassie default,John Carraclough,0,0,0,,{TIME:1307160,1310705}Hot tea and milk are waiting\Nfor us. Come on!
